<section>
  <h2>Overlay placement (most flexible, and slowest)</h2>
  <p>Overlay placement attaches the marker elements in an internal
    node generated by <code>Guide.js</code>, which is appended to the
    <code>body</code>.
  </p>

  <p>This is best used when:</p>
  <ol>
    <li>the <code>position</code> CSS property of the target, and its parent, can not be <code>absolute</code>, or <code>relative</code></li>
    <li>design isn't responsive, or all devices support fixed positioning</li>
  </ol>

  <p>The marker uses <strong>absolute</strong> positioning in overlay
    placement.</p>

  <%= erb :"advanced/samples/edge", locals: { placement: 'overlay' } %>
  <%= erb :"advanced/samples/grid", locals: { placement: 'overlay' } %>
  <%= erb :"advanced/samples/nodes", locals: { placement: 'overlay' } %>
  <%= erb :"advanced/samples/blocks", locals: { placement: 'overlay' } %>

</section>

<script>
  $(function() {
    Guide.setOptions({
      tutor: {
        enabled: false
      },
      controls: {
        inMarkers: false
      },

      marker: {
        placement: 'overlay'
      }
    }).fromDOM($('body')).show();

  });

</script>